result.name: Han Dao Restaurant

reviews.text: It's across from Panda Hotel & near my shopping area. There are pix of the food, so language is no problem. Friendly staff & helpful too.
I was expecting a vietnamese food but it turns out chinese.style.
Best tasting beef and wanton noodles! The beef brisket and chicken curry was as good too. Chao fan and the stir fried noodles were also good.
Cheap food here...but tasty
A no-nonsense neighbourhood restaurant that has been around for at least a decade and probably two. It serves pretty good Chiu Chow style beef brisket and offal noodles.
